'''Bror Jace''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] who was one of the original members of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron's]] second reformation, briefly serving as [[Rogue Four/Legends|Rogue Four]].

==Biography==
A [[Thyferra/Legends|Thyferran]] native, Jace was a prominent member of [[Zaltin Corporation]]. His membership in the [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] was brought about by equal parts piloting skill and political concession. The [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] wished to keep the [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] cartels happy and so put one person from each corporation on the squadron. Though dedicated to the New Republic cause, Bror was an arrogant man who was convinced that he was the most skilled of Rogue Squadron's new recruits. Throughout his time in the squadron, he found a rival and equal as a [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] in [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]], whom Bror regarded as the only new pilot in the squadron who could truly compete with him. In the end, Bror won the rivalry with twenty-two kills to Corran's twenty-one.

After the [[Second Battle of Borleias]], Bror received a message from home, saying that the family patriarch was dying. En route, however, his [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] was pulled from [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Immobilizer 418 Interdictor-class Heavy Cruiser|Interdictor cruiser]] [[Corusca Rainbow|''Black Asp'']] and destroyed. This, the rest of the squadron would later find out, was a ruse to bring him home to work with the [[Ashern]] rebels within Zaltin to plan a civil war against [[Xucphra Corporation|Xucphra]], Zaltin's rival, and [[Ysanne Isard]].

Jace rejoined Rogue Squadron to help bring down Isard and free his home planet. He flew with the squadron during its battle with the ''[[Lusankya/Legends|Lusankya]]''. After the Rogues' victory at Thyferra, when [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] and the rest of the squadron were choosing whether to stay with the squadron, Jace chose to leave the squadron again to head the formation of a [[Thyferran Aerospace Defense Force]].
